Comment.Text: Processing chain The signal is processed in several stages : 1. The signal is split by channels and two linear combinations are calculated : CPz - POz and 4 x Oz - (O1 + O2 + POz + Iz) 2. For each stimulated frequency, both of these characteristics are split into parts where the frequency was stimulated and the rest. 3. The signal is cut into windows of 1s every 100ms. The value of the signal is squared, averaged and square rooted.

Classifier Training After the training session, this scenario will process the recorded signal and train several classifiers. Each classifier works with one stimulation frequency and is capable to discern whether it is stimulated or not. All of the classifiers will be saved in []. If you want them to be saved in a different place, you should modify the paths in the three Classifier Trainer boxes. Training will begin automatically after the scenario finishes. You can verify classification rates in the terminal window.
